snippet.textDisplay:
This video proves the real meaning of the whole album, and no, it's not about sex, drugs and women: this video is for us, the fans - just like the ''Rolling Stone'' video.
He's back at the ''House of Balloons'' but he's struggling while being there - not like in his 2012 video ''The Zone'' - where we can see a chick at the house of balloons crying in the end.
Now he's the one who doesn't enjoy being there anymore, and just wants to leave, the people holding him are the die-hard fans that keep saying he'll go back to the Trilogy/Kiss Land times, no, he's not going back, he wants to be someone different, do something different (just like in every album he releases) - during almost the whole album he struggles with this, I guess some people do not pay attention to the lyrics and just make crazy theories that make no sense.
Even the video ends with ''I don't need it anymore'' and the camera pointing the balloons.
